headline: Prediction: Trump's Victory Should Pave the Way for Wells Fargo to Shed Its Asset Cap, Which Has Cost the Bank Billions in Profits
summary: Aside from the Great Recession and the bank failures of last year, few issues in the recent banking era have been more scandalous than Wells Fargo's (NYSE: WFC) infamous phony-accounts scandal.  Since that scandal came to light in 2016, Wells Fargo has dealt with consent orders, paid billions in fines, and done its best to overcome a reputational nightmare.  The Fed first imposed the asset cap on Wells Fargo in 2018, barring the bank's total assets from surpassing roughly $1.95 trillion.
